[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Another large deployment exists at China Mobile.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] The Open Networking Foundation was founded in 2011 to promote SDN and OpenFlow.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] At the 2014 Interop and Tech Field Day, software-defined networking was demonstrated by Avaya using shortest-path bridging (IEEE 802.1aq) and OpenStack as an automated campus, extending automation from the data center to the end device and removing manual provisioning from service delivery.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] SDN architectures decouple network control (control plane) and forwarding (data plane) functions, enabling the network control to become directly programmable and the underlying infrastructure to be abstracted from applications and network services.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] The OpenFlow protocol is one of the protocols used in SDN technologies.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] The explosion of mobile devices and content, server virtualization, and the advent of cloud services are among the trends driving the networking industry to re-examine traditional network architectures.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Many conventional networks are hierarchical, built with tiers of Ethernet switches arranged in a tree structure.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] This design made sense when client-server computing was dominant, but such a static architecture may be ill-suited to the dynamic computing and storage needs of today's enterprise data centers, campuses, and carrier environments.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Within the enterprise data center, traffic patterns have changed significantly.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] At the same time, users are changing network traffic patterns as they push for access to corporate content and applications from any type of device, connecting from anywhere, at any time.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] model, which may include a private cloud, public cloud, or some mix of both, resulting in additional traffic across the wide-area network.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Users are increasingly employing mobile personal devices such as smartphones, tablets, and notebooks to access the corporate network.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] IT is under pressure to accommodate these personal devices in a fine-grained manner while protecting corporate data and intellectual property and meeting compliance mandates.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Enterprises have enthusiastically embraced both public and private cloud services, resulting in unprecedented growth of these services.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Many enterprise businesses want the agility to access applications, infrastructure and other IT resources on demand and discretely.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] IT planning for cloud services must be performed in an environment of increased security, compliance and auditing requirements, along with business reorganizations, consolidations and mergers that can rapidly change assumptions.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Providing self-service provisioning, whether in a private or public cloud, requires elastic scaling of computing, storage and network resources, ideally from a common viewpoint and with a common suite of tools.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] requires massive parallel processing on thousands of servers, all of which need direct connections to each other.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] is fueling a constant demand for additional network capacity in the data center.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Operators of hyperscale data center networks face the daunting task of scaling the network to previously unimaginable size, maintaining any-to-any connectivity within a limited budget.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] emerged, the need for larger data centers has increased the energy consumption of those facilities.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] applying existing routing techniques to dynamically adjust the network data plane to save energy.
[src:software-defined-networking/software-defined-networking] Also techniques to improve control plane energy efficiency are being researched.
